                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2436: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-24T18:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received September 24, 1.50 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram of September 22, 5 p.m. The Ministry of Finance has given me
                    assurance verbally and in writing that Hsu En-yuan is authorized to renew the
                    existing Chicago Bank loan of $5,000,000 and also to negotiate for supplementary
                    loan of $25,000,000 contemplated by original contract.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
